Anything else you can say? I'm just about to run out 
of questions. Anything that we need to touch on? I

46:13.509 --> 46:33.117
think that the petroleum engineering curriculum 
is a very good curriculum for a young person in that

46:13.509 --> 46:33.117
he is trained how to drill wells, how to produce 
fluids from wells, how to separate those fluids,

46:33.839 --> 46:39.749
process them at the surface, ship them down 
pipelines to the consumer. He learns about fluid

46:40.731 --> 46:43.075
flow through porous media. He learns about 
geology and economics. With that background, he

46:46.881 --> 46:52.090
can be a petroleum engineer and produce oil and 
gas. He could produce groundwater just as well. He

46:57.058 --> 46:59.863
could produce geothermal energy just as well. He 
could do mineral leaching, mineral processing

47:00.502 --> 47:04.370
just as well. He could work in institute lignite 
gasification or coal gasification just as well.

